genresAdvancedInfo.name: swiss reggae
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Swiss reggae is a genre of music that emerged in the 1980s, influenced by the Jamaican reggae scene. It is characterized by its laid-back rhythms, socially conscious lyrics, and a focus on peace and love. Swiss reggae artists such as Phenomden, Dodo, and Open Season have gained international recognition and continue to bring their unique blend of Swiss and Jamaican culture to the world.
